    en: { name: "Flour Mill", role: "Reconstructed watermill", zone: "Western park",
         desc: "A reconstructed water-powered flour mill at the foot of Tell Qasile, modelled on the mills that worked in northern Israel for centuries — water diverted through a conduit turns a wheel that drives the upper millstone. Such mills produced 30–50 kg of flour an hour and were vital social and economic centres.",
